'''Velocity Gaming''' (aka '''VLT''') was formed in 2017. It was registered as an [[:Category:India|Indian]] Esports organization in 2019 by Manoj "[[SENTINEL]]" Kasyap. 

The organisation were initially into ''Rainbow Six Siege'', later they invested into the ''Indian Esports Scene'' by supporting players of variety of games like ''Valorant, Counter-Strike'', etc.

On December 24th, 2020 they rebranded to '''Team Mahi''' (aka '''TM''').<ref name="team mahi">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=N9-xSGMd_T4|title=About Team Mahi|date=2020-12-24|author='''Team Mahi'''|language={{Flag|usuk}} English}}</ref>

On May 30th, 2021 they rebranded again to '''Velocity Gaming''' (aka '''VLT''').<ref name="velocity gaming 2021">{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/CPgJjlVHCHf/|title=Velocity Gaming Roster #VLTFTW|date=2021-05-30|author='''Velocity Gaming'''|language={{Flag|usuk}} English}}</ref>

